Atlassian Bitbucket Data Center and Server Remote Code Execution (RCE)  Vulnerability
PAN-OS GlobalProtect Gateway and Portal Denial of Service Vulnerability
Column1:
1/23 CH - QID Available (733584)

high-severity denial-of-service (DoS) vulnerability in Palo Alto Networks PAN-OS affecting the GlobalProtect Gateway and Portal components. The flaw allows an unauthenticated remote attacker to repeatedly send crafted network traffic that causes the firewall to crash or enter maintenance mode, disrupting traffic and remote access services. Exploitation requires no credentials or user interaction and has proof-of-concept (PoC) code publicly available. There are reports of automated scanning and potential targeting of exposed systems, but Palo Alto Networks states it has not seen confirmed malicious exploitation in the wild yet.
